we can setup some aliases for commands,
like long command we used on pre lesson tto formatting log command!

git config --global alias.(alias name) "the command"        //global means for all our repositories


git config --global alias.lg "log --pretty=format:'%an %h on %cd'"   //we should not use git on nested command!
                                                                     //he knows he is git!

git config --global alis.unstage "restore --staged ."                //define "unstage" to unstage all the current change to pre state
                                                                     //restore stage area to pre commit!

Note: check the config file to find the alise we defined:
      git config --global -e